# Linting & Formatting

## Basic Requirements
- ESLint + Prettier enforced in CI; no warnings in PRs
- Use TypeScript ESLint with strict recommended configs
- Style and import order automated; do not hand-format

## Mandatory Actions
- Add project-wide `.editorconfig` and consistent end-of-line settings
- Enable `no-explicit-any`, `no-floating-promises`, `no-unused-vars`
- Enable `import/no-cycle`, `import/order`, and `eslint-plugin-security`

## Forbidden Behaviors
- Disabling rules without justification and scope (file- or line-level)
- Committing with lint errors or format diffs

## Example Config
```json
{
  "extends": ["eslint:recommended", "plugin:@typescript-eslint/strict", "prettier"],
  "plugins": ["@typescript-eslint", "import", "security"],
  "rules": {
    "@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any": "error",
    "@typescript-eslint/no-floating-promises": "error",
    "no-unused-vars": ["error", { "argsIgnorePattern": "^_" }]
  }
}
```
